pYadis 0.1
==========

An automatic backup utility.

Author: James Crickmere
Email: james.crickmere@googlemail.com
Copyright: See 'COPYING' file.
URL: http://pyadis.googlecode.com/

Installing
----------

1. Extract pYadis-<version>.tar.gz.
2. Open a shell and cd to the pYadis-<version> folder.
3. Run: sudo python setup.py install
4. Run `pyadis-config` to configure the programme.
5. Schedule the command `pyadis-deamon` to start automatically on user login, or
   use crontab or similar to schedule the command `pyadis-deamon once` to run
   as frequently as you want new and updated files to be backed up.

Uninstalling
------------

Run: python setup.py uninstall

